Tony Hatch and Jackie Trent wrote a string of chart-topping hits for the world's biggest stars . 
  They were married for more than three decades and wrote for Frank Sinatra, Dean Martin and Shirley Bassey . 
  The couple wrote the theme tune for Australian soap Neighbours . 
  Trent died last month aged 74 and Hatch was banned from her funeral by her second husband . 
  Colin Gregory says she never forgave him for cheating on her . 
  He also says he denied her credit for some of the songs they wrote . 
 